00:10:59.226 --> 00:11:03.366
That might be building a new well for water, a school

00:11:03.366 --> 00:11:08.506
for the children, a hospital or just buying better farming equipment.

00:11:10.341 --> 00:11:15.681
What this means is that the farmers who sell through Fairtrade are

00:11:15.681 --> 00:11:22.161
guaranteed a more stable income and they can invest in their farms, and it gives

00:11:22.161 --> 00:11:28.101
them a chance to provide a better, more stable future for them and their family.

00:11:29.194 --> 00:11:34.113
These higher prices for Fairtrade are paid ultimately

00:11:34.113 --> 00:11:40.863
by consumers, by you, by me, by the people who are choosing the banana,

00:11:40.893 --> 00:11:45.363
the chocolate bar, the tea, or the coffee with the Fairtrade logo.

00:11:47.403 --> 00:11:50.943
And as you probably know, the price difference between

00:11:51.213 --> 00:11:56.043
non-Fairtrade and Fairtrade is often not very large.

00:11:57.153 --> 00:12:01.953
So you can pay a little more for your products and feel

00:12:01.953 --> 00:12:05.313
that you are supporting a farmer and an honourable mission.

00:12:06.036 --> 00:12:09.156
The farmer gets paid fairly, you get to feel that you

00:12:09.156 --> 00:12:14.166
are making an ethical purchase and you feel better about yourself, and

00:12:14.586 --> 00:12:19.196
there is a stamp from Fairtrade, so maybe it even tastes better too.

00:12:20.106 --> 00:12:21.516
Everyone's a winner, right?

00:12:21.696 --> 00:12:24.396
What could possibly be the issue with this?

00:12:25.153 --> 00:12:29.070
Well, it isn't always as rosy as it seems.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:36.210
And while I don't think anyone is disagreeing with the fact that farmers should be paid

00:12:36.210 --> 00:12:42.480
a fair rate for their work and that everyone should have a sustainable future, there

00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:49.470
are those that say that Fairtrade actually isn't a very effective way to achieve this.

00:12:50.846 --> 00:12:57.086
Firstly, there is the complaint that it doesn't actually help that much.

00:12:58.346 --> 00:13:03.656
There is a cost for the farmers to achieve the Fairtrade certification,

00:13:04.496 --> 00:13:09.836
both a bureaucratic and administrative cost, but also financial.

00:13:11.140 --> 00:13:15.731
For coffee, it's estimated that it costs around 3 cents per pound.

00:13:16.961 --> 00:13:23.681
Now, that might not sound like a lot, but it does add up and for some farmers

00:13:24.191 --> 00:13:28.901
there is evidence to suggest that there is zero long-term benefit.

00:13:30.453 --> 00:13:35.493
Secondly, there is a lack of transparency around how the

00:13:35.493 --> 00:13:42.113
Fairtrade premium is spent, how the extra money is spent by the cooperative.

00:13:43.493 --> 00:13:48.283
Fairtrade, the organisation, doesn't monitor this, doesn't

00:13:48.283 --> 00:13:55.888
monitor how the money is spent and even though the funds should be allocated democratically by the

00:13:55.888 --> 00:14:02.518
members of the cooperative, they aren't always spent on the things that will have the most impact.

00:14:03.538 --> 00:14:08.488
So from time to time, they are instead spent on buildings

00:14:08.488 --> 00:14:12.988
and salaries as opposed to schools or medical clinics.

00:14:14.739 --> 00:14:19.659
Thirdly, which is one that I think is actually a pretty interesting

00:14:19.659 --> 00:14:26.349
criticism is that Fairtrade isn't actually a very effective way of transferring

00:14:26.349 --> 00:14:31.839
money from the people who consume the products to the people who produce them.

00:14:34.089 --> 00:14:41.019
There was an experiment done in San Francisco where they asked people how much more

00:14:41.049 --> 00:14:47.019
they would be willing to pay for a cup of Fairtrade coffee compared to a normal one.

00:14:48.639 --> 00:14:49.239
The answer?

00:14:50.244 --> 00:14:55.344
The average person was willing to pay an extra 50 cents per cup.

00:14:56.764 --> 00:14:59.579
But the maximum amount of money from that same

00:14:59.579 --> 00:15:04.589
